//- /
extends ../layouts/layout.pug

block head
  //- highlight.js styles
  link(rel='stylesheet', href='/styles/highlight.css')
  link(rel='stylesheet', href='/styles/main.css')

  title clairefro
  meta(name='description', content='clairefro\'s corner of the internet')
  meta(name='twitter:title', content='clairefro')
  meta(
    name='twitter:description',
    content='clairefro\'s corner of the internet'
  )
  meta(property='og:title', content='clairefro')

block content
  img.avatar(
    src='/assets/me.png',
    alt='Blurred portrait of Claire Froelich with a bird sitting on hand',
    style='display: block; margin: 0 auto; max-width: 166px'
  )
  #greeter
    .textbox
      h1 Claire Froelich

  div
    :markdown-it
      I'm a self-taught tinkerer with a background in linguistics and interpreting. I believe language and technology can help us get over language and technology.

      Borges is my muse, and Jonathan Basile's [digital Library of Babel](https://libraryofbabel.info/) is my favorite corner of the world wide web.

      I like simple solutions. This website uses vanilla everything. Just html, markdown, file-based routing, and CSS. You can read why in [this blog post](/blog/p/look-ma-no-react-why-i-recoded-my-portfolio-site-with-vanilla-everything). The color scheme is inspired by [*yaki-imo*](https://www.google.com/search?q=%E7%84%BC%E3%81%8D%E8%8A%8B&source=lnms&tbm=isch&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwi1iojH8e31AhVGkokEHa3QAHwQ_AUoAXoECAIQAw&biw=1063&bih=539&dpr=2.5) (baked Japanese sweet potato).
